Meet <b>Devon</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>This star athlete resides at <a href='/home/?user=obairashid'>44177-A Maple Street</a> in Westridge. When he's not scoring three-pointers or touchdowns, he can often be found singing! He makes people laugh with his spot-on renditions of popular songs, and singing to himself when he's alone relaxes him.<br><br>Since moving to Millsberry on December 23, 2005, Devon has set an example for his friends by keeping his house remarkably clean. He has a pretty busy schedule, with school and sports every week, but he still manages to keep things tidy. Not only does he always put things away when he's done using them, but he also sets aside time every weekend to listen to some rap or reggae and get his house in order. <br><br>He ends up hosting a lot of spontaneous get-togethers because his home is always ready for visitors! After school or a game, his friends come over and hang out. Devon has a couple of enviable plasma TVs, perfect for watching sports on. <br><br>When it comes to basketball or football, Devon is a total team player. His teammates respect him for being such a dedicated leader who always puts the team's success first. And he has serious natural talent. Thanks to some amazing last-minute plays and great defensive moves, he is responsible for some truly unforgettable moments in <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/">Millsberry Academy</a> sports history!  <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Devon, and congratulations on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
